results.name: a(n) is the cototient of n^3.
comment: For n^k, n^k - EulerPhi(n^k) = n^(k-1)*(n-EulerPhi(n)), or cototient(n^k) = n^(k-1)*cototient(n). A similar relation holds for Euler totient function.
link: Vincenzo Librandi, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
formula: a(n) = n^2*Cototient(n) = A051953(n^3) = n^3 - EulerPhi(n^3) = Cototient(n^3).
results.author: _Labos Elemer_, Mar 02 2000
